===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|wif|lang=enm}}, {{term|wiif|lang=enm}}, {{term|wyf|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|wif|wīf|woman, female, lady, wife|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|wībą||woman, wife|lang=gem-pro}}, possibly from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|gʰʷí₂bʰ-||shame, pudenda|lang=ine-pro}} (compare Tocharian A/B {{term|kip|lang=xto}}/{{term|kwīpe||shame, genitals, female pudenda|lang=txb}}).<ref>Douglas Q. Adams, ''A Dictionary of Tocharian B'' (Amsterdam-Atlanta: Rodopoi, 1999), 238.</ref><ref>Klaus Totila Schmit & Klaus Strunk, “Toch. B ''kwī̆pe'' ‘Schaum, Schande’, A ''kip'' ‘Schaum’ und germ. *''wīƀa'' ‘Weib’”, ''Indogermanica Europaea: Festschrift für Wolfgang Meid'' (Graz: Institut für Sprachwissenschaft der Universität Graz, 1989), 251-284.</ref> Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|wife||wife|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|wiif||wife, woman|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|wüf||wife, woman|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|wijf||woman, female|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|Wief||woman, female|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Weib||woman, wife, female|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|viv||woman|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|viv||woman|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|fo|-}} {{term|vív||wife, woman|lang=fo}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|víf||woman|lang=is}}.

